description:
&lt;p&gt;City Health Care Partnership CIC (CHCP) is looking to recruit enthusiastic and self-motivated registered nurses, including newly qualified nurses. We are able to offer a range of positions and experiences in community nursing providing nursing care in patients own homes and within treatment rooms (for example wound care, phlebotomy and a range of clinical skills delivered in treatment rooms within health centres)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer services across Hull and the East Riding of Yorkshire and aim to work with candidates to match our opportunities to the nurses own career aspirations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of community nursing is not essential and each successful candidate will have a named mentor and an individually tailored development plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CHCP CIC is committed to developing its clinical workforce and therefore offers the successful candidate opportunities for further study and career progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Various hours are available across West and East Hull localities, with bases at Haltemprice, Priory Park and Longhill Health Centre andin the Holderness Locality with bases at Hornsea and Withernsea. Please ensure that you state your preferred location on your application.&lt;/p&gt;
